criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age higher than 18 years old:

          -  A medical diagnosis of PD confirmed according to the Movement disorders criteria;

          -  PS defined as at least 10 degrees of lateral trunk flexion that can be reduced by
             passive mobilization or supine positioning (PS≥10) (Doherty et. al., 2011);

          -  Camptocormia defined as a flexion (at least 5°) in the sagittal plane originating in
             the thoracolumbar spine, (classified as upper and lower), manifesting during standing
             and walking and completely subside in recumbent position (Pandey et. al., 2016);

          -  Hoehn & Yahr (H&Y) stage <4 in "ON" medication phase.

          -  Informed consent to participate in the study

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe dyskinesia or "on-off" fluctuations;

          -  PD medication modification in the 3 months preceding enrollment into the study;

          -  Need for assistive devices to rise from a chair or bed; somatic sensation deficits
             involving the legs;

          -  Vestibular disorders or paroxysmal vertigo; other neurological, orthopaedic or
             cardiovascular co-morbidities
